18/01/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- The Albanian Parliament on Sunday (18 January) rejected a no confidence motion filed by the opposition against the government of Prime Minister Fatos Nano. 
A total of 76 parliamentarians voted against the motion, while 50 supported it and one abstained.The opposition demanded the vote in light of the recent tragedy in the Ionian Sea, in which at least 20 illegal emigrants lost their lives on their way to Italy.
In other news, Albanian President Alfred Moisiu used his meeting with European diplomatic representatives on Friday to urge Western countries to soften visa requirements for Albanians.Moisiu reiterated the government's commitment to strengthening border security and fighting organised crime and human trafficking. 
(ATA - 19/01/04, ATA - 18/01/04)
